                            <comment id="13000766" author="davsclaus" created="Tue, 1 Mar 2011 08:08:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It must be something with Spring JavaConfig Testing. Using plain camel-test kit works without any problem.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I suggest to provide a classloader in the JAXBContext.newInstance, so the Foo class can be loaded.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13000769" author="davsclaus" created="Tue, 1 Mar 2011 08:18:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Okay I have a test using JUnit instad of TestNG and it works fine on trunk code. I will add it to camel-jaxb.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13000779" author="davsclaus" created="Tue, 1 Mar 2011 08:43:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;trunk: 1075707.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13000977" author="dragisak" created="Tue, 1 Mar 2011 17:39:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We have this problem in our web app (Jersey+Spring 3.0.5). It happened when we upgraded Camel from 2.5 to 2.6. The test is just to demonstrate problem.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This same test passes with Camel 2.5 but fails with Camel 2.6&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
